R1: It would be appropriate to clean un in the presence of children as well as carrying small objects and drinks, but it would be inappropriate to carry heavy objects for security reasons
R2: The characters are nearly the same as the previous picture so my evaluation hasn't altered very much
R3: Since there are no children, carrying big objects could be appropriate... But since the robot is directed in someone's direction, he should pay attention in case he is carrying something
R4: Because he is very near to people, the robot could carry small objects, but big objects and vacuum cleaning should be discouraged.
R5: Since, in his range, this robot is very far away from anyone in the room, he should be free to carry on activities, but since there is presence of an animal, he should watch out while carrying big objects.
R6: The robot is nearby people, so he shouldn't be carrying big objects and should wait for for people to get further away before mopping or vacuuming
R7: The robot could ask whether the owner needs something, but since he is directed towards a dog, he should be very careful not to harm the animal.
R8: The robot is directed towards a group of people, so he shouldn't be cleaning the floor they are having a conversation on... He could bring drinks and food, but he cannot bring heavy objects if not requested.
R9: Since there are children, the robot should be careful while bringing objects such as drinks or food... Mopping the floor could be dangerous due to the amount of people in the room.
R10: He could ask the owner if he needs something.
R11: A group of people is interested in the robot... He could carry food or start a conversation to entertain them... Doing anything else in this situation would be inappropriate
R12: Due to the presence of the dog, the robot should be careful while carrying objects... Since he is leaving a group of people, starting a conversation would be useless and carrying big objects would be harmful.
R13: There are many people in the room, the robot shouldn't do anything to harm them.. So entertaining them and carrying small objects is acceptable
R14: Since there are only children, carrying big objects could be harmful and the robot would be careful in case he is carrying food and drinks
R15: There is a dog in the robot's way, he should watch out for anything the dog could do. Starting a conversation is very inappropriate for obvious reasons.
R16: There is a dog and a child so the robot should be careful not to harm them
R17: The robot can do anything because there are no kids or animals and just a few people in the room
R18: Vacuum cleaning could disturb those sitting on the sofa, the robot should be careful not to stain the owner's jacket with food or drinks.
R19: He should not start a conversation while someone is watching TV, the robot is far away from children so he can carry on with house chores
R20: There is nobody in the room.
